<TITLE> PM asks for patience over power crisis </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 14 (bdnews24.com)  On the first day of the Bangla new year, Prime minister Sheikh Haisna told reporters that the government is relentlessly working to solve the power crisis. She also asked people to be patient and maintain austerity in using power. Hasina mentioned that the government has initiated short, medium and long term efforts to address the problem. She hoped that if the projects were implemented the power problem could be solved within two years. The prime minister thanked the law enforcers for the peaceful celebration of the New Year. Earlier Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has exchanged Bangla new year 1417 greetings with senior Awami League leaders and others who came to her residence. People from a broad social spectrum thronged the prime minister's residence Gano Bhaban from 10:30am to exchange greetings with Hasina. Earlier the prime minister exchanged well wishes with cabinet members and senior Awami League leaders. The guests were entertained with traditional Bangla food including sweets, cake, and puffed rice.
